Common.Highlight.Common.Text: The most iconic, highly connected, wellpositioned building in downtown Minneapolis
Prime full block location between Nicollet Mall, 7th Street, 8th Street and Marquette Ave
57 Stories
1.2M SF Class A+ Office Space
166K SF Prime Retail Space
281 Room 4-Star Hotel
23,000 SF Indoor Urban Park
50,000 Visitors Per Day
Easily accessible via parking, light rail stations, bus routes and the most traveled skyways in Minneapolis
Approximately 3,500 employees office in the premiere, Class A building and another 118,000 employees within a half mile of IDS

189 micro-unit apartments directly above retail.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
The Duffey is a mixed-use redevelopment of the historic CJ Duffey Paper
Co building in the heart of Minneapolis’s North Loop neighborhood. The site
is located on the highly traveled Washington Ave and sits between 5th & 6th
Ave. The Duffey will consist of 189 micro unit apartments and approximately
22,274 SF of retail in the existing building.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
In addition to the existing structures, the Duffey offers one of the most unique
retail opportunities within Minneapolis: a ground up building at the corner
of Washington Ave & 5th Ave. The corner building floor plan is up to 9,383
square feet with the possibility for single or two-story structure.
